@wake2skate22 @chynna_weierstall and I drove to Powder Springs near Atlanta today. It was too hot for me to stay focused and I didn’t land a thing.  They killed it as always. Had fun skating the gap and leaving with a sunburn instead of a good clip 😰

We had a little Miami flavor for today’s skate session in celebration for @wake2skate22 in staying forever young 🎉. Always a great time with these amazing friends 🌴❤️‍🔥
Thanks for celebrating our lady, @sk8er_samy @robertmichaelarias @chynna_weierstall

Skating has been a struggle lately physically and mentally. Because of chronic pain my trick vocabulary has been cut way down and so has the amount I can skate. It’s hard when the one thing you love to do the most feels like it’s slipping away. Trying my best to stay positive but it’s not always easy. 

Very thankful for this past weekend in Ohio with @brandigr2 & @wake2skate22 . No matter how hard things get these girls can always make me laugh and smile ❤️.

Wasn’t able to skate as much as I wanted this year. Struggled a lot physically and mentally but still made a lot of great memories. Thankful for my amazing friends and family who continue to believe in me, kept me going, laughing and smiling even on the hardest days ❤️. Also thank you to all my sponsors for continuing to support me @factionskatecompany @createoriginals @chromawheels @modernskate . To more growth and great memories and rollerblading in 2024.
Chill first clip of the year. Didn’t feel as good as I was hoping yesterday but thanks @wake2skate22 for motivating me and always being down to sesh the quarters & half pipes with me ❤️

Went to Charlotte area for warmer weather and had ourselves a blast. Quick sesh but fun af. Phil and I decided to go back to back on the rail, and now that I look at the footage, I realize he was subtly one-upping me on each pass. 🤪🤣 too good. 
chynna came over for a moment to show us what’s what and then took over filming Thank you Chynnaaaaa 🙏🏼🤘🏻 

Let’s do this again soon!
